When it comes to the Happy Little Camper in our lives, natural is better, which is why we’ve created baby products that are naturally safe and naturally better for your baby's skin and for the environment.​ This means that not only is your baby comfortable in Happy Little Camper, but also safe and free from harsh chemicals. Knowing the facts, consider making a better choice for your baby’s bottom by making Happy Little Camper your go-to natural baby care brand. SUSTAINABLE DIAPERS - We source only the purest, sustainably sourced pulp and natural cotton which are all approved by Mother Nature. Feel good about using Happy Little Camper with plant-based ingredients! Why don't we include wetness indicator strips on our diapers? You know those little wetness indicator strips on your baby’s diaper? Have you noticed that Happy Little Camper diapers don’t have them? There’s a good reason for that! While the wetness indicator offers the convenience of knowing when baby is wet, the strips are actually made out of harmful chemical dye. One of the Happy Little Camper promises are that our diapers contain NO dye, which is why there are no wetness indicators in our diapers. Moms and Dads, we’re pretty confident that you know when your baby is wet without needing an indicator strip made of harsh dyes to tell you. Did you know that babies urinate up to20 times a day? This means that baby should be checked every 2 to 3 hours. Usually, wet diapers will tend to be heavy, you can either pad the diaper with a hand, squeeze it gently. When squeezing or padding the diaper, it’ll be obvious that the diaper is wet from the moisture soaking the inner diaper layers. Opening up the diaper to double check is also advised and there’s always the good ol’ nose-to-diaper smell test! Happy Little Camper = No Dyes or Harmful Chemicals Happy Little Camper products do not contain harmful chemicals because our diapers +wipes are made with natural, hypoallergenic ingredients. We don’t use indicator strips or any dye that can penetrate baby’s skin and potentially cause harm to their fragile organs. Our products have been dermatologically tested, so you can trust that our diapers + wipes are skin-loving and safe for baby. What is diaper rash? Diaper rash grows in warm and moist places on your baby’s bottom and appears in patches of inflamed red skin. A baby’s skin is extra sensitive and can overreact to exposure to certain environmental factors and chemicals. Naturally, some babies have more sensitive skin than others and tolerate products differently. Common causes of nappy rash include; Diaper is not changed frequently enough, Skin sensitivity to harmful chemicals found in unnatural diapers and/or Change in diet/introduction to new foods Steps to limit the likelihood of nappy rash include; Changing your baby’s diaper more frequently and/or Using natural products free from harsh chemicals. Happy Little Camper is super soft on your baby’s sensitive skin there are no added fragrances, harmful dyes, and chlorine, latex, phthalates, parabens contained in our diapers. Our products are made of the purest, sustainably sourced pulp and natural cotton which are all approved by Mother Nature. What is Eczema and how is it caused? Eczema also known as atopic dermatitis is a very resilient skin condition that makes your skin red and itchy. One in five children develop Eczema with a large majority having an outbreak before the age of five. Eczema is long lasting (chronic) and gets worse the longer it is present making it harder to control. Your genetic background is a strong predictor of eczema. If both of your parents have it, there is an 80% chance that you may develop it as well. Eczema generally flares as a result of environmental factors including change in climate to either cold, dry conditions or hot, humid ones. This is because eczema affects the skins’ ability to provide moisture and defend it from irritants, and allergens. In some cases, food allergies may play a role in causing Eczema, particularly in children. Our diapers are packed full of safe ingredients and nutrients to soothe and hydrate your baby’s’ sensitive skin. Most importantly, they are dermatologically tested and hypoallergenic meaning they are safe and soft on your baby’s bottom!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent diapers and wipes, even better price
reviews.reviewText: Just started using these diapers on my 3 month old daughter after her earth's best size 1s ran out and she needed to size up to size 2. These diapers are super soft and comfy for her, the side stays are very stretchy and grip very well. They also do not leak as bad as the earth's best when it comes to blow-outs. 2 major factors I look for when buying her diapers is 1. Non-toxic, hypoallergenic and 2. Price point. There is no better deal out there than the happy little campers month supply with the nontoxic wipes. It is so convenient to get the diapers and wipes right to my door, especially when they are also an affordable, quality product.

reviews.reviewText: I really wanted to love these diapers because they’ve been one of the brands that hasn’t given my baby a rash, but I just can’t.
